\label{thm:main}
Let $S$ be a log del Pezzo surface of rank one over an algebraically closed field $k$ of characteristic five.
Then the following hold.
\begin{enumerate}
    \item[\textup{(1)}] $S$ is not log liftable over the ring of Witt vectors $W(k)$ if and only if $\operatorname{Dyn} (S) =2[3,2]+[3]+[2]+[2^4]$, $[4,2]+[3,2^5]+[3,2]+[2]$, $[2,4]+[2,3,2^2]+[3]+[2^4]$, or $2[2^4]+(\dagger)$, where $(\dagger)$ is listed in Table \ref{tab:dagger}.
    \item[\textup{(2)}] The isomorphism class of $S$ is uniquely determined by its Dynkin type except when $\operatorname{Dyn} (S)=2[2^4]+ [2^n]+[2+n; [2], [3], [5]]$ for some $n \geq 0$.
    In these cases, the isomorphism classes of del Pezzo surfaces correspond to the closed points of $\mathbb{P}^1_k \setminus \{0, 1, \infty\}$ for each $n \geq 0$.
    \item[\textup{(3)}] $S$ is not log liftable over $W(k)$ but there exists a log del Pezzo surface of rank one over $\mathbb{C}$ with the same Dynkin type as $S$ if and only if $\operatorname{Dyn} (S) = 2[2^4]+[3]$ or $2[2^4]+[2, 4]$.
\end{enumerate}

