\label{LacA.19}
Let $S$ be a projective surface with klt singularities and $\sigma \colon \widetilde S \to S$ be the minimal resolution.
Take a reduced and irreducible curve $C \subset S$ such that $(K_S+C \cdot C) \leq 0$.
Then one of the following holds.
\begin{enumerate}
    \item[\textup{(1)}] $C \subset S^\circ$.
    \item[\textup{(2)}] For each $s \in S$, $\sigma$ is a log resolution of $(S, C)$ at $s$ or $E_\sigma$ satisfies one of (a)--(c) in Definition \ref{def:almostlc} at $s$.
\end{enumerate}
Moreover, if $C$ has a singularity in $S^\circ$ in addition, then $C \subset S^\circ$.

